2094class InverseAffineIterMapTransformer {
2095 public:
2096 explicit InverseAffineIterMapTransformer(Analyzer* analyzer) : analyzer_(analyzer) {}
2097
2098 Map<Var, PrimExpr> operator()(const Array<IterSumExpr>& iter_map,
2099 const Array<PrimExpr>& outputs) {
2100 ICHECK(iter_map.size() == outputs.size());
2101 std::vector<const IterMapExprNode*> post_dfs_order = ReverseTopologyOrder(iter_map);
2102
2103 // initialize back propagation accumulator
2104 for (const IterMapExprNode* node : post_dfs_order) {
2105 backprop_.Set(GetRef<IterMapExpr>(node), Integer(0));
2106 }
2107 for (size_t i = 0; i < iter_map.size(); i++) {
2108 backprop_.Set(iter_map[i], outputs[i]);
2109 }
2110
2111 // run back propagation
2112 for (const IterMapExprNode* node : post_dfs_order) {
2113 if (node->IsInstance<IterSumExprNode>()) {
2114 Visit_(Downcast<IterSumExpr>(GetRef<IterMapExpr>(node)));
2115 } else {
2116 ICHECK(node->IsInstance<IterSplitExprNode>());
2117 Visit_(Downcast<IterSplitExpr>(GetRef<IterMapExpr>(node)));
2118 }
2119 }
2120 return std::move(inverse_);
2121 }
2122
2123 private:
2124 void Visit_(const IterSumExpr& iter_map_expr) {
2125 PrimExpr input = backprop_.at(iter_map_expr) - iter_map_expr->base;
2126
2127 // Case 1: Propagate to the input node directly when the sum expression has only one components
2128 if (iter_map_expr->args.size() == 1) {
2129 const auto& source = iter_map_expr->args[0];
2130 backprop_.Set(source, backprop_.at(source) + input);
2131 return;
2132 }
2133
2134 // Case 2: If the sum expression has multiple components, check the fuse pattern and then split
2135 // the sum expression for each components.
2136 // For example, consider the iterator i1[dom = (0, 16)], i2[dom = (0, 8)], fusing i1 and i2
2137 // we will have i1_i2_fused[dom = (0, 64)]. During back propagation, we need to split the
2138 // propagated value to get the corresponding components of i1 and i2, which are
2139 // floordiv(i1_i2_fused, 8) and floormod(i1_i2_fused, 8), respectively.
2140 CheckFusePattern(iter_map_expr);
2141 for (size_t i = iter_map_expr->args.size(); i > 0; i--) {
2142 const IterSplitExpr& split = iter_map_expr->args[i - 1];
2143 PrimExpr prop_value = floordiv(input, split->scale);
2144 // the first part has the same extent as the split expression, floormod is not needed
2145 if (i > 1) {
2146 prop_value = floormod(prop_value, split->extent);
2147 }
2148 backprop_.Set(split, backprop_.at(split) + prop_value);
2149 }
2150 }
2151
2152 std::vector<const IterMapExprNode*> ReverseTopologyOrder(const Array<IterSumExpr>& iter_map) {
2153 std::vector<const IterMapExprNode*> post_dfs_order;
2154 std::unordered_map<IterMapExpr, bool, ObjectPtrHash, ObjectPtrEqual> visited;
2155
2156 std::function<void(const IterMapExpr&)> fvisit = [&](const IterMapExpr& expr) {
2157 if (visited[expr]) {
2158 return;
2159 }
2160 visited[expr] = true;
2161 if (const auto* sum_expr = expr.as<IterSumExprNode>()) {
2162 for (const IterSplitExpr& child : sum_expr->args) {
2163 fvisit(child);
2164 }
2165 } else {
2166 const auto* split_expr = expr.as<IterSplitExprNode>();
2167 ICHECK(split_expr);
2168 if (const auto* source = split_expr->source->source.as<IterMapExprNode>()) {
2169 fvisit(GetRef<IterMapExpr>(source));
2170 }
2171 }
2172 post_dfs_order.push_back(expr.get());
2173 };
2174 for (const IterSumExpr& expr : iter_map) {
2175 fvisit(expr);
2176 }
2177 std::reverse(post_dfs_order.begin(), post_dfs_order.end());
2178 return post_dfs_order;
2179 }
2180
2181 void Visit_(const IterSplitExpr& iter_map_expr) {
2182 PrimExpr input = backprop_.at(iter_map_expr) * iter_map_expr->lower_factor;
2183 const IterMark& source = iter_map_expr->source;
2184 if (source->source.as<IterSumExprNode>()) {
2185 IterSumExpr source_expr = Downcast<IterSumExpr>(source->source);
2186 backprop_.Set(source_expr, backprop_.at(source_expr) + input);
2187 } else {
2188 Var source_var = Downcast<Var>(source->source);
2189 if (inverse_.count(source_var)) {
2190 inverse_.Set(source_var, inverse_.at(source_var) + input);
2191 } else {
2192 inverse_.Set(source_var, input);
2193 }
2194 }
2195 }
2196
2197 /*
2198 * \brief Check the fuse pattern of sum_expr. We assume components of sum_expr is sorted in
2199 * descending order of lower_factor.
2200 */
2201 void CheckFusePattern(const IterSumExpr sum_expr) {
2202 if (sum_expr->args.empty()) {
2203 return;
2204 }
2205 PrimExpr expected_scale = sum_expr->args.back()->scale;
2206 for (size_t i = sum_expr->args.size(); i > 0; i--) {
2207 ICHECK(analyzer_->CanProveEqual(sum_expr->args[i - 1]->scale, expected_scale));
2208 expected_scale *= sum_expr->args[i - 1]->extent;
2209 }
2210 }
2211
2212 Analyzer* analyzer_;
2213 Map<IterMapExpr, PrimExpr> backprop_; // the accumulator of backpropgation
2214 Map<Var, PrimExpr> inverse_; // the result of inverse transformation
2215};
2216
2217Map<Var, PrimExpr> InverseAffineIterMap(const Array<IterSumExpr>& iter_map,
2218 const Array<PrimExpr> outputs) {
2219 Analyzer analyzer;
2220 return InverseAffineIterMapTransformer(&analyzer)(iter_map, outputs);
2221}
